race.comment: The ultra consistent TALTARNI FIELDS (1) lumped 60kgs in a $250k Magic Millions race over this trip at the Gold Coast three weeks ago and did a good job to hang on for third after showing pace. In the money at all six runs at Doomben and he looks beautifully treated after the claim. Very hard to tip against. PETITE PALACE (18) went to Warwick and was far too good in a BM70 over 1100m last time out. Consistent mare who drops 4.5kgs today to take on this better field. Gets a soft run behind the pace and is a live chance. STREAK OF WINNING (13) scored first-up then held that form when beaten under a length in a BM70 over today's journey at the Sunshine Coast more recently. Bit of a tricky draw but with luck he should be in the finish. LAYDOWNLILY (11) made late inroads to get up for fourth when fresh from a spell over 1000m at the Sunny Coast a fortnight ago. Twice a winner at this trip so she is right in the mix.
